videos.description: Udoka Azubuike sends back a Lindell Wigginton shot with authority.
videos.headline: Kansas' Azubuike rejects Wigginton

videos.description: Udoka Azubuike takes the fast-break pass from Devonte' Graham and finishes with big dunk.
videos.headline: Kansas' Azubuike slams it home

videos.description: Two big dunks by Malik Newman and Lagerald Vick makes Allen Fieldhouse loud early in the second half.
videos.headline: Back-to-back slams fire up Jayhawks crowd

videos.description: Donovan Jackson sinks 3-pointers on back-to-back possessions to bring the Cyclones within 1 of Kansas.
videos.headline: Iowa State's Jackson knocks down big 3s

videos.description: Lindell Wigginton drains a 3-pointer from the corner off the assist from Nick Weiler-Babb.
videos.headline: Iowa State's Wigginton drills corner 3

videos.description: Malik Newman blocks the Donovan Jackson jumper then finishes the fast break with a layup to extend the Jayhawks' lead.
videos.headline: Kansas' Newman gets block, clutch layup

videos.description: Malik Newman's 27 points are the most off the bench by a Kansas player in the last 20 seasons and helps the Jayhawks defeat Iowa State 83-78 on Tuesday night.
videos.headline: No. 12 Kansas hold off Iowa State
